answers about professional boundaries in health and social care settings</span></h3><p class="sc-eFegNN jgBUGG pf-190_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-192_">Here at The Mandatory Training Group, we receive many questions about professional boundaries in health and social care settings. We have selected a few of these questions and answered them below.</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-193_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eGPXGI dIjtdz pf-194_"><div class="sc-iCfMLu eZKDwH pf-195_ pf-icon-right" data-scrolling="false" data-multiple="false" data-pf-type="Accordion"><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-196_"><button type="button" class="sc-jRQBWg fpohrn pf-197_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="a559773c-b6cb-44c5-a127-f87e600001dd" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>Why is it important to maintain boundaries with clients?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="a559773c-b6cb-44c5-a127-f87e600001dd" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-gKclnd dMSgnu pf-199_"><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-200_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eGPXGI dIjtdz pf-201_"><p class="sc-eFegNN jgBUGG pf-202_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-204_">There is a need for clear boundaries to protect the therapeutic process and to keep the relationship professional. Boundaries protect clients from getting taken advantage of due to vulnerability and also protect therapists from being sued by patients.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-205_"><button type="button" class="sc-jRQBWg fpohrn pf-206_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="27f87e60-0001-4d9e-a04b-2d8ae8e2bbe3" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>What are the types of professional boundaries?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="27f87e60-0001-4d9e-a04b-2d8ae8e2bbe3" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-gKclnd dMSgnu pf-208_"><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-209_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eGPXGI dIjtdz pf-210_"><p class="sc-eFegNN jgBUGG pf-211_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-213_">These are the few major boundaries that may affect your practice and behaviour:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-fXEqDS fVXmAe pf-214_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-215_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-217_">Client focus</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-218_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-220_">Self-disclosure</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-221_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-223_">Dual relationships</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-224_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-226_">Working within your competence</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-227_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-229_">Looking after self.</span></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-230_"><button type="button" class="sc-jRQBWg fpohrn pf-231_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="4b2d8ae8-e2bb-43e1-99d2-63880d5448aa" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>How do you maintain professional boundaries with clients?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="4b2d8ae8-e2bb-43e1-99d2-63880d5448aa" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-gKclnd dMSgnu pf-233_"><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-234_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eGPXGI dIjtdz pf-235_"><p class="sc-eFegNN jgBUGG pf-236_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-238_">These are ways to set and maintain professional boundaries:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-fXEqDS fVXmAe pf-239_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-240_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-242_">Assess your boundaries first</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-243_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-245_">Communicate clearly</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-246_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-248_">Respond to boundary crossings in real-time</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-249_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-251_">Keep your relationships professional</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-252_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-254_">Learn to say “No”.</span></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-255_"><button type="button" class="sc-jRQBWg fpohrn pf-256_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="d263880d-5448-4adc-b138-e948cc9086a1" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>How do you maintain professional boundaries in health and social care?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="d263880d-5448-4adc-b138-e948cc9086a1" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-gKclnd dMSgnu pf-258_"><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-259_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eGPXGI dIjtdz pf-260_"><p class="sc-eFegNN jgBUGG pf-261_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-263_">You can maintain professional boundaries in health and social care by:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-fXEqDS fVXmAe pf-264_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-265_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-267_">Acting trustworthy and responsible in all your dealings with and for clients.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-268_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-270_">Being truthful and honest in your interactions with clients.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-271_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-273_">Respecting the clients' rights as individuals.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-274_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-276_">Ensuring all current and potential clients have an equal opportunity to access and benefit from your service.</span></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-277_"><button type="button" class="sc-jRQBWg fpohrn pf-278_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="38e948cc-9086-415d-9e39-2e0f63131c62" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>What are the benefits of professional boundaries?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="38e948cc-9086-415d-9e39-2e0f63131c62" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-gKclnd dMSgnu pf-280_"><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-281_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eGPXGI dIjtdz pf-282_"><p class="sc-eFegNN jgBUGG pf-283_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-285_">Professional boundaries help ensure the safety of both the worker and service user and reduce anxiety as the roles and boundaries of the relationship are clear, allowing for a therapeutic environment rooted in mutual respect.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-286_"><button type="button" class="sc-jRQBWg fpohrn pf-287_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="392e0f63-131c-42b3-849f-814197c2ac17" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>Why is it essential to maintain clear professional boundaries between a practitioner and a client?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="392e0f63-131c-42b3-849f-814197c2ac17" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-gKclnd dMSgnu pf-289_"><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-290_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eGPXGI dIjtdz pf-291_"><p class="sc-eFegNN jgBUGG pf-292_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-294_">Professional boundaries are limits which protect the space between a worker's professional power and their client's vulnerability. Problems for care workers that can arise if these boundaries aren't maintained are: Becoming overly involved or attached to a client. Showing unusual behaviour towards a client.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-295_"><button type="button" class="sc-jRQBWg fpohrn pf-296_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="9f814197-c2ac-47b9-8676-b7f7cc4db495" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>How do you maintain professional boundaries with patients?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="9f814197-c2ac-47b9-8676-b7f7cc4db495" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-gKclnd dMSgnu pf-298_"><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-299_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eGPXGI dIjtdz pf-300_"><p class="sc-eFegNN jgBUGG pf-301_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-303_">These are ways to maintain professional boundaries with patients:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-fXEqDS fVXmAe pf-304_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-305_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-307_">Don't pursue a sexual or close emotional relationship with a patient or someone close to them.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-308_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-310_">Act quickly to re-establish boundaries if a patient misbehaves.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-FNXRL brLfuZ pf-311_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-313_">Avoid sharing personal information with patients in person or online.</span></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-314_"><button type="button" class="sc-jRQBWg fpohrn pf-315_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="76b7f7cc-4db4-454b-9e88-0576d58d40d8" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>Why is it essential to work within professional boundaries?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="76b7f7cc-4db4-454b-9e88-0576d58d40d8" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-gKclnd dMSgnu pf-317_"><div class="sc-iJKOTD qriss pf-318_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eGPXGI dIjtdz pf-319_"><p class="sc-eFegNN jgBUGG pf-320_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-322_">Relationship-centred working may cause uncertainty for some about how to carry out their roles and responsibilities. Professional boundaries help us to make sense of this and can be described as the 'boundary between what is acceptable and unacceptable for a professional both at work and outside work'.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-323_"><button type="button" class="sc-jRQBWg fpohrn pf-324_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="162af288-cf09-45e6-909c-e5f6af236741" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>Do you provide face-to-face training for professional boundaries in health and social care settings?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="162af288-cf09-45e6-909c-e5f6af236741" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-gKclnd dMSgnu pf-326_"><p class="sc-eFegNN jgBUGG pf-327_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-329_">All our training courses and packages for professional boundaries in health and social care settings are delivered online. We do not provide any classroom or face-to-face training.</span></p></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-330_"><button type="button" class="sc-jRQBWg fpohrn pf-331_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="e6d09ce5-f6af-4367-81fc-1446a1896d85" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>Where can I find online training courses for professional boundaries in health and social care settings?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="e6d09ce5-f6af-4367-81fc-1446a1896d85" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-gKclnd dMSgnu pf-333_"><p class="sc-eFegNN jgBUGG pf-334_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fmciRz hKEAti pf-336_">The Mandatory Training Group is the leading UK provider of accredited online professional boundaries essential in health and social care settings training courses for all sectors, including health, safety and wellbeing, social care, education, local government, and many more.
